0.6.0 (2025)
- Full port to KDE Plasma 6 / Qt 6 / KDE Frameworks 6
- QML-based UI replacing Qt Widgets (compactRepresentation + fullRepresentation)
- Settings dialog integrated into standard Plasma settings (Search Engines, Shortcuts, About)
- Wayland support: primary selection via wl-clipboard, browser activation via xdg-activation-v1
- Clipboard reading via wl-paste (Wayland primary selection) with Klipper D-Bus fallback
- Favicon download via KIO::FavIconRequestJob (handles all formats including SVG)
- URL opening via KIO::OpenUrlJob with xdg-activation token for proper foreground focus
- Global shortcut registration via KGlobalAccel
- Config pages in standard Plasma settings dialog (no separate window)
- Search engine list fully configurable from settings; built-in engines are examples only

0.5.2 (10.10.2009)
- new AUTHORS file, updated README file

0.5.1 (30.09.2009)
- global shortcut for triggering a query works again
- added another possibility for a global shortcut to open the manual query dialog
- added some more search engines to the default list

0.5 (10.09.2009)
- automatic download of icons for the search engines

0.4.2 (31.08.2009)
- fixed bug which caused plasma to crash

0.4.1 (31.08.2009)
- alphabetical sorting of search engines in the menus
- added a few more search engines to the default list
- some of the search engines are now hidden by default

0.4 (30.08.2009)
- new configuration interface for search engines
- possibility to add, remove and edit search engines
- possibility to hide some of the configured search engines
- position (main menu / submenu) configurable per engine

